Results
The association between PM2.5 and SBP was stronger for those who reported high levels of stress, but this interaction was significant only in the Southwest Detroit neighborhood. Southwest Detroit residents who reported low stress showed 2.94mmHg (95% CI: −0.85, 6.72) increase in SBP for each 10$\mu$g/m3 increase in 2-day prior PM2.5 exposure. Those who reported high stress showed 9.05mmHg (95% CI: 3.29, 14.81) increase in SBP for each 10$\mu$g/m3 increase in PM2.5 exposure.
