Odds ratios of low birthweight of 1.02 (95% CI, 1.01–1.03) and 1.07 (95% CI, 1.01–1.12) with concentration increases of 1µg/m3 for NO2 and PM10 respectively. Raised but insignificant risks of very preterm birth were found with PM10 (relative risk ratio=1.08; 95% CI, 1.00 to 1.17 per 1µg/m3) and NO2 (relative risk ratio=1.01; 95% CI, 1.00 to 1.03 per 1µg/m3). An inverse association between mean birthweight and mean annual NO2(−1.24g; 95% CI, −2.02 to −0.46 per 1µg/m3) and PM10 (−5.67g; 95% CI, −9.47 to −1.87 per 1µg/m3). SO2 showed no significant associations.
