two routes. Moreover, the exposure of all three pathways in children was greater than in adults. The excess cancer risk (ECR) of Pb, Ni, As, Cd, and Cr was beyond the safety limit (10−6 to 10−4), indicating cancer risk in both adults and children. This study provides detailed composition data and the first report on FW particles during the SF period and their potential impact on human health in Changchun city.},
